# React + TypeScript Standards

## Rules
- Prefer small reusable components over repeated markup
- Keep props typed explicitly
- Avoid any
- Avoid large monolithic page files when a component can be extracted cleanly
- Preserve existing behavior unless asked to change it
- Keep className logic readable
- Use useMemo/useCallback only when they actually help
- Avoid dead code
- Avoid duplicated styles across pages

## When editing
- do the minimum required to improve quality
- do not refactor unrelated logic
- keep naming consistent with the project
